social_posts.post_text: I’m blessed to spend so much time with my family and continue to keep creating so many great memories. We work hard, build a lot of wild things, we have shared our life with the entire world though our tv shows/social media and I wouldn’t change a thing. I got into racing super late in life by accident. When I had this opportunity I took it extremely serious. I thought when I grew up I was going to be in the military (that’s what I always wanted to do) I wanted to start with sniper training then see where that took me. This is why you see on everything I do a giant American flag with a large Support Our Troops. Anyway I don’t mean to make this long but where ever you are in life look back on your memories and be thankful for the ones you have created because life is short. Thank you for the ones who have supported me though out the years🙌🏻. #family #memories #racing #trucks #military

Our widebody Lincoln Continental build😳

Not everyone needs expensive CAD or expensive tools to create different unique things. My dad @deberti and I enjoy working together everyday, today we went and got ABUNCH of tape, card board, and other craft items to create a vision for both of us to see.

What you see if about 6 hours of work, it’s not perfect and it’s not beautiful but this is how great things are built.

We still don’t know 100% if we are going to widebody this car.. yes it’s a rare car, and a lot of y’all had some pretty bad comments to say on my last post. The thing is we like to be different with our builds and it’s been that way since I was a kid working with my dad in the shop. 

I do want everyone’s feedback because we truly base our builds off of that, but please give feedback and understand we are not going to “ruin, destroy or hurt” this car. We are giving this a car a new life that is going to set it aside from any Lincoln Continental out there. 

I’m blessed to be working side by side with my dad and I am excited for this build series. If you’re a company reading this and might have awesome parts to help us please dm me. If you are one of my awesome followers give us good advice instead of being so negative👊🏻

BEST GUESS GETS A RIDE!

Driving this truck is quite amazing, it revs from 1k to 10k in about a millisecond which is crazy! Fun fact that’s really not to fun.. driving this truck around town is harder than doing 80mph sideways because it has a 7.25” Nascar triple disk clutch. If you don’t know what that means it basically means there is no ridding the clutch when taking off.. it’s all or nothing. 

This is great for performance but not as a daily driver lol. Everything on this TRD motor is 100% created to race. The internals are as light as possible which is another reason why it revs so high and so fast. This power plant is amazing and sounds like no other motor! 

I hope everyone has a blessed weekend!!

Should this be factory on trucks??? What would you put in this bumper drawer?
If you have been interested in this read the info below.

A big goal in 2024 is to finally have our patented bumper drawer available to purchase. We get lots of questions “are you ever going to come out with this” and the answer is YES. 

Most don’t know the crazy steps it takes from a full patent in every state, to perfecting something that requires so much fabrication. We have had quite a few production versions made, it’s just not 100% where we want it yet but it is very close. 

When this comes out we want it to be one of the nicest products to hit the market and to do that it just takes time. @deberti and I will keep everyone updated as we go through the steps. 

As of now Ford Trucks will be the first kit available. What brand will be next? That’s up to everyone on here.

The original DeBerti Raptor is in Saudi Arabia! 

This truck set the bar for the ford raptor industry, we created and machined these fenders and they are one of the most popular aftermarket fenders on the market. 

If you play @forzahorizonofficial you will also see the DeBerti Raptor. A few million people drive this truck a month just in the video game which is so cool for my pops and I! 

Fun fact this truck is what jump started my career. This was the first truck @deberti and I teamed up and built after my dad took about a 15 year break. He started a company called TRENZ and built many trucks yearly. When he sold it he decided to take a break.

Watch how a surf boat is made😳!!

We flew across the country to document the process of how @centurionboats creates their surf boat from start to finish and it’s UNBELIEVABLE!!! 

@deberti and I have a whole new respect for the marine world. We got to watch our boat be made by hand with all the custom DeBerti accessories they created.

Aside from the amazing process, one of the coolest parts of the tour was at lunch time they stopped to have a bible study with all the employees. We joined it and met some amazing people. It’s awesome to work with a company that cares for their people just as much as they care for their quality work.

If you get a second and want to watch this awesome episode head over to our YT channel “Brad DeBerti” and checkout the step by step process👊🏻
